# Command defuddle

## What does this command do:

Get the main content of any page as Markdown

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: `npm install defuddle`

## Command path

For Fedora run: `defuddle`

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/kepano/defuddle

## Command options

```
defuddle parse <input> [options]
```

Input can be a local HTML file path or a URL.

| Option               | Alias | Description                                      |
|----------------------|-------|--------------------------------------------------|
| `--output <file>`    | `-o`  | Write results to file instead of stdout          |
| `--markdown`         | `-m`  | Convert content to markdown format               |
| `--md`               |       | Alias for --markdown                             |
| `--json`             | `-j`  | Output as JSON with metadata                     |
| `--property <name>`  | `-p`  | Extract specific property (title, description, domain) |
| `--debug`            |       | Enable debug mode with detailed processing info  |
| `--lang <code>`      | `-l`  | Set preferred language using BCP 47 format       |

# Parse a URL and output as markdown
defuddle parse https://example.com/article --markdown

# Parse a local HTML file and save to file
defuddle parse page.html --output result.md --markdown

# Get JSON output with all metadata
defuddle parse https://example.com/article --json

# Extract a specific property (e.g. title)
defuddle parse https://example.com/article --property title

# Enable debug mode
defuddle parse https://example.com/article --debug
